<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="395" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2136/349.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Furniss</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-05"><hi rend="italic">December 5,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Root informs Minister Furniss that in the absence of naval vessel of
                            any European power having interests in Haiti, and upon urgent occasion
                            or request for protection, the American naval forces will afford
                            temporary protection and refuge from immediate violence in the same
                            manner as to American citizens and interests similarly menaced.</p>
                    </div>
